items

java.util.List items()

This is the python analogue to Java's Map.entrySet() method. Instead of returning a Set of Map.Entry objects, this instead should return a List of Object[] arrays of size 2. The first element in the array is the key, the second is the value.

Returns:
List of Object[2] (aka key/value tuples)
